data.reddit:
Not being a hypochondriac, but in this one episode of monsters inside me, one of this woman’s first symptoms was sunlight hurting her eyes, and headaches. I’ve had this all the time and just thought I was sensitive to uv light, cause some days everything just seems way too bright and I get headaches and even wearing sunglasses I still squint. 

But she has seizures but I’ve never had one so I know it’s not what she has. 

Just asking though, is it not normal? Like I know not everyone has it, but is it bad?

Female age 18, 

Non smoker but my dad smokes and I get second hand sometimes, 

Non drinker, 

No medications, 

Weight: usually between 115 and 98 lbs (I have trouble keeping my weight cause I have emetophobia, 

Race: Caucasian, (German, Norwegian, Irish etc)

Duration of complaint: since I was in elementary school.

Existing conditions; insomnia, anxiety, scoliosis, gerd, there’s probably more but I haven’t been to the doctor in a while.

I also have ptsd from various events.

Also sometimes I twitch lmao, like I get a chill up my spine for no reason and it makes me shake my head. I almost forgot to add that but it happens a lot and just happened again. Happens at least 15 times a day maybe more. Happens to my dad too.
